            "help_text": "Funding level enacted in the previous fiscal year.",
            "field_type": "text",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": true,
            "draft_value": "$7,250,000,000",
            "rationale": "The FY2026 enacted level is $7,250,000,000 as per the SMD Topline Funding History and the pre-filled value annotation.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r1c73b64b76154c4a94c3e5dd0cbf306e:1a0ea32b2889",
            "label": "FY27 funding justification",
            "help_text": "Narrative explaining why this funding is necessary.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Requesting $9.0 billion for NASA Science to restore stability after FY26 disruptions and maintain U.S. leadership against rapid Chinese space expansion.\n* Every dollar invested in NASA Science returns approximately three dollars to the U.S. economy while supporting a highly skilled industrial and scientific workforce.\n* Funding supports peer-reviewed Decadal Survey priorities that ensure the U.S. remains the global leader in planetary defense and discovery.\n* Sustained investment is a fundamental public responsibility that advances national security and economic competitiveness in ways no private entity can replicate.",
            "rationale": "Justification uses the $9B ask amount, references the 24% increase needed over FY26 enacted, and incorporates advocacy points regarding the 3:1 ROI and competition with China.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "microsoft_forms:01:r5594ba8e591c46dbb3a906f2c9c9e792:60ff9f47b4d1",
            "label": "CA-23 Impact",
            "help_text": "Describe the impact of this request on California's 23rd Congressional District.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* NASA Science obligated over $17.3 million in CA-23 from FY2023 to FY2025, supporting high-tech jobs and local economic activity.\n* Major district recipients include Vertex Aerospace LLC ($76.9M total contract value) and Environmental Systems Research Institute ($7.3M across 7 contracts).\n* Pci Productions LLC in Edwards provides $6.8M in essential support for the Armstrong Flight Research Center, a critical regional asset.\n* Academic and medical research at Loma Linda University ($3.5M in grants) ensures CA-23 remains at the forefront of NASA's scientific mission.",
            "rationale": "Cites the $17.3M total obligation figure for CA-23 and specific local recipients including Vertex Aerospace, ESRI, Pci Productions, and Loma Linda University from the provided spending data.",
            "confidence": "high"
          }
        ]
